fn_tests.input_infer:
serialize_some(self, value: &T) where T: Serialize; // T can be any serializable type including custom structs, enums and primitives. 
Test input ranges: (valid values for T: any struct or enum implementing Serialize, basic types like i32, f64, char; invalid types: non-serializable types like functions, raw pointers, or unsupported types like i128/u128; sizes: small size for basic types, larger complex structures for checking performance; maximum T instances for serialization should also be considered).
